5000|$|In August 1920, a {{group of}} armed men tried to kill Ayyubi in the {{province}} of Hawran in southern Syria. They accused him of treason for <b>accepting</b> <b>office</b> under the [...] "French Mandate". The assassination attempt, however, failed at convincing him to step down, and he remained at his post until 1922, after which he became Minister of Justice in the pro-French cabinet of Prime Minister Subhi Barakat, keeping his post until a national uprising took place against the French Mandate in 1925.|$|E
