50|$|The King made various {{attempts}} to induce Pitt {{to come to}} his rescue by forming a ministry, but without success, and at last had recourse to Lord Rockingham. When Rockingham agreed to <b>accept</b> <b>office,</b> the king dismissed Grenville in July 1765. He never again held office.|$|R
